{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b13b25b6-334c-40aa-b044-8bf2973bb35f","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform the VSTest switches are replaced by platform-native options. You also need to add the corresponding NuGet extension packages.\n\n**New command:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nEverything after `--` is passed directly to the Microsoft.Testing.Platform host.\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n\n| Old mechanism | New package |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n\n**Key changes:**\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` / `--blame-hang-timeout` → `--hangdump` / `--hangdump-timeout`\n- `--filter` still works (VSTest filter syntax is supported via a compatibility layer), but the native alternative is `--treenode-filter`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0840be61-ca7e-45ad-a64f-7aa52fad43c3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling changes, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n1. `--filter` → `--filter` (same, but the syntax is slightly different with the new platform)\n2. `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (built-in)\n3. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you configure it differently\n\n\n4. `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n5. `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n6. `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, there's a distinction between running through `dotnet test` as a wrapper versus running directly with `dotnet run`. The `dotnet test` command translates some options automatically, but the native command-line interface has different option names. I should clarify the exact syntax for Microsoft.Testing.Platform—the filter approach depends on whether I'm using `dotnet test` with the new pass-through syntax or running the test project directly, and I need to be precise about which filter syntax is actually supported versus what's just compatibility mapping. I'll wrap this up with a clear summary of the available reporting options and their package dependencies.","outputTokens":1326,"requestId":"982F:254503:177184:1EDE59:69FFD87C"},"id":"e1a2d878-cf80-4d3b-aed4-413987386380","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:00:03.253Z","parentId":"89944c54-db75-4ee5-9d8c-167983534e44"}
